# 🔒 Mafia Game — Full Security & Architecture Audit

**Auditor**: Senior Security Architect / Red Team  
**Date**: 2026-03-03  
**Repo**: `SAMIHZS/mafia-game` (branch: `main`)  
**Stack**: Node.js + Express + Socket.IO + MongoDB + Vanilla JS Frontend  
**Hosting**: Railway (backend), static frontend via `http-server`

---

## Executive Summary

The Mafia game is a real-time multiplayer WebSocket application with REST API endpoints, JWT-based session management, and MongoDB persistence. The codebase demonstrates decent security awareness (role privacy, input validation, state machine checks) but has **15 critical/high-severity issues** that would be trivially exploitable in production. The application is **NOT production-ready** in its current state.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Go/No-Go: ❌ NO-GO** — Fix all Critical and High issues before deploying with real users.

---

## 📊 Phase 13 — Security Scores

| Category | Score | Verdict |
|---|---|---|
| **Security** | **32/100** | 🔴 Failing |
| **Architecture** | **58/100** | 🟡 Needs work |
| **Production Readiness** | **25/100** | 🔴 Not ready |

