## 🧪 Phase 10 — Attack Simulations

| Attack | Vulnerable? | Exploit Method | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| Brute force room codes | ✅ Yes | `GET /api/room/:code` — no rate limit | Rate limit + CAPTCHA |
| JWT token theft | ⚠️ Low | `sessionStorage` — no XSS steal. But XSS in chat (CRIT-04) could access it | Fix XSS |
| XSS injection | ✅ Yes | Chat message `<script>` tag via `innerHTML` | HTML escape server-side |
| Privilege escalation | ⚠️ Low | Host check uses `socket.id` comparison — solid | — |
| Race condition | ✅ Yes | Simultaneous votes during `setTimeout(500)` gap | Add mutex |
| API flooding (DoS) | ✅ Yes | Spam `POST /api/room` | Rate limiter |
| Replay attack | ⚠️ Low | JWT has `iat` and `exp` — replaying old valid tokens works within 24h window | Shorter token TTL + token blacklist |
| WebSocket hijacking | ⚠️ Medium | No `io.use()` auth — any script can connect | Add WS auth middleware |
| Room code prediction | ✅ Yes | `Math.random()` is reversible | Use `crypto.randomBytes` |
| State desync | ⚠️ Medium | Disconnect during phase transition → stale timers | Add state reconciliation |

---

## ⚙️ Phase 11 — Performance & Scalability

| Check | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|
| Memory leaks | ⚠️ Risk | `joinAttempts` Map never pruned — grows indefinitely |
| Unclosed timers | ✅ Fixed | Phase timers cleared on room delete |
| WebSocket cleanup | ✅ Good | Grace period + explicit leave handler |
| Caching | ❌ None | No cache headers on any response |
| Load balancing | ❌ No | Socket.IO with in-memory adapter (only 1 instance) |
| CDN | ❌ No | Static assets served from same origin |

**Fix for `joinAttempts` memory leak**:
```javascript
// Add cleanup interval
setInterval(() => {
  const now = Date.now();
  for (const [ip, entry] of joinAttempts.entries()) {
    if (now > entry.resetAt) joinAttempts.delete(ip);
  }
}, 300000); // every 5 min
```

